communicated by:
ProMED from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The cause of this outbreak of foodborne illness in Assam is not stated. However, it seems that because the illnesses began with gastrointestinal symptoms on the same day as the meeting, the cause is likely either a preformed bacterial toxin disease, such as staphylococcal food poisoning, or chemical poisoning. - Mod.LL

ProMED would appreciate further information about this outbreak as details emerge. - Mod.SH

